title: Sources: Warriors expect Butler to play Game 4
description: The Warriors are expecting Jimmy Butler to make his return Monday night in Game 4 against the Rockets, sources told ESPN.
author: Ohm Youngmisuk

title: Source: WR Johnson to Browns after strange '24
description: The Browns reached agreement on a one-year contract with free agent wide receiver Diontae Johnson on Monday.
author: ESPN

title: 'Class of 92' graduates aim for more Crucible glory
description: Snooker's legendary 'Class of 92' - John Higgins, Mark Williams and Ronnie O'Sullivan - have won 14 world titles between them and are all in contention in 2025.

title: Champions League run 'a beautiful story' but Arteta wants 'much more'
description: Mikel Arteta says Arsenal "want much more" in the Champions League before they take on Paris St-Germain in the semi-finals in "one of the biggest games the Emirates Stadium has seen".

title: FOURTEEN-YEAR-OLD Suryavanshi hits record IPL century
description: Fourteen-year-old prodigy Vaibhav Suryavanshi hit a jaw-dropping 35-ball century in the Indian Premier League on Monday, firing Rajasthan Royals to victory against Gujarat Titans.

title: Benn 'two beds down' from Eubank Jr after precautionary hospital visit
description: Chris Eubank Jr is "doing well" in hospital after his hard-fought points victory over Conor Benn at Tottenham Hotspur Stadium on Saturday night.

title: Twins get season-high 17 hits, Bailey Ober allows 1 run in 7 2/3 innings in 11-1 rout of Guardians
description: Jonah Bride had three of Minnesota's 17 hits, Bailey Ober allowed one run in 7 2/3 innings and the Minnesota Twins rolled to an 11-1 victory over the Cleveland Guardians on Monday night. Minnesota had 10 players with hits, the first time the Twins had done that since last June against the Athletics. Six players had at least two hits, including Ryan Jeffers, who had a two-run homer and three RBIs.
author: JOE REEDY
